                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Just a thought:
<br />
Check what your connection specific DNS suffix is in the advanced TCP/IP properties.  Make sure it matches that of the campus network, or just add it as a searchable DNS suffix.
<br />

<br />
I assume when you mentioned Linux that was the campus servers etc. and not your computer.  I have no idea how to get to the TCP/IP settings on a Linux box.
<br />

<br />
The ports for EQ above are right.  I had to enable port forwarding on my router for TCP ports 1023-7000. 
<br />

<br />

